    {
      "id": "urn:article:1-s2-0-s2666603021000063-main",
      "type": "schema:ScholarlyArticle",
      "title": "A new data security algorithm for the cloud computing based on genetics techniques and logical-mathematical functions",
      "authors": [
        "Fursan Thabit",
        "Sharaf Alhomdy",
        "Sudhir Jagtap"
      ],
      "year": "",
      "doi": "10.1016/j.ijin.2021.03.001",
      "journal": "",
      "abstract": "With the rapid development of distributed system technologies, one of the biggest challenges facing the digital\nworld is ensuring the security of sensitive and con fidential data during transport and storage, which are\nconsidered the most critical challenges facing cloud computing. There are many techniques to enhance data security on cloud computing storage environment. Encryption is the most signi ficant method for data protection.\nTherefore, many available encryption algorithms are used to provide security, integrity, and authorized access\nusing many methods such as DNA. However, they still have some limitations. In this paper, a novel variant of\ncryptography techniques is designed to improve cloud computing security by using two layers of encryption. Thefirst layer is inspired by Shannon 's theory of diffusion and confusion by the involvement of logical operations,\nsuch as (XOR, XNOR, shifting) with split the original plaintext and key into equal parts. The second layer is\ninspired from structures of genetics based on the Central Dogma of Molecular Biology for cryptographic purpose\nthrough simulation of the natural processes of genetic cryptography (translation from binary to DNA bases),transcription (regeneration from DNA to mRNA), and translation (regeneration from mRNA to protein). The\nexperimental results enhanced data security that can be used to secure applications on cloud computing. The\nproposed algorithm 's experimental results presented a strong security level, an apparent enhancement of cipher\nsize and execution time compared to existing techniques widely used in cloud computing.",
      "keywords": [
        "Cloud computing security",
        "Cryptography",
        "Genetics techniques",
        "Logical-mathematical functions"
      ],
      "objective": [
        "Moreover, to enhanced security issues in the cloud, this paper introduces a novel variant of cryptography techniques to improve the security of cloud computing."
      ],
      "problem": [
        "The central population is established depending on the problem under study, and the suitability of each group is evaluated using the fitness function [ 6,7]."
      ],
      "methodology": [
        "For enhancing the security of could computing, there are many techniques such as cryptography which is the primary factor of security data in the cloud.",
        "Cryptology is a mathematical technique for security information management such as encryption, quality of data and authentication.",
        "Cryptography offers various morerobust methods, and it is possible to use techniques to provide these security services [ 2]."
      ],
      "contributions": [
        "Therefore, the major contributions of this paper can be summarized as follows: 1) A novel 256-bit cryptography technique based on CDMB technique with logical-mathematical function is introduced in this paper. 2) A novel 256-bit secret key generation technique based on DNA sequence is introduced in this paper 3) Security analysis and experimental results of Purpose work have been explained in this paper to verify its ef ficiency over the existing techniques."
      ],
      "futureWork": [
        "In future work, the proposed algorithm can be improved by reducing the space complexity to meet the memory requirements 'challenge."
      ],
